{
  "texts": [
    "Using Stable Diffusion V1.5 as the foundational model in the fine-tuning phase of the diffusion model and as a baseline for subsequent qualitative and quantitative comparisons.",
    "We utilized the ADSSFID-49 dataset to fine-tune the improved diffusion model.",
    "Specifically, the improved diffusion model employed a new composite loss function to learn from this dataset, continuously reducing the loss during training.",
    "This allowed the model to acquire knowledge in respect of the aesthetic score, decoration style, and spatial functionality, resulting in a new diffusion model for aesthetic interior design, known as the aesthetic interior design diffusion model (i.e., AIDDM).",
    "During the model utilization stage, designers can use the AIDDM for design generation and modification."
  ]
}